Traditional Programming vs Artificial Intelligence

| Feature          | Traditional Programming         | Artificial Intelligence (AI)          |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Working Method   | Human writes all rules manually | System learns from data automatically |
| Logic            | Fixed logic                     | Learns and improves                   |
| Data Handling    | Uses predefined conditions      | Finds patterns from data              |
| Flexibility      | Less flexible                   | More flexible                         |
| Decision Making  | Based on coded instructions     | Based on learning and prediction      |
| Accuracy         | Good for fixed tasks            | Better for complex tasks              |
| Learning Ability | Cannot learn automatically      | Can learn from experience             |
| Best For         | Simple repetitive tasks         | Smart decision-making tasks           |


========

Simple Example
Traditional Programming
Problem:

Check whether number is even or odd.

Programmer writes rule:

IF number % 2 == 0
    Even
ELSE
    Odd


Computer only follows instructions.


===========

Artificial Intelligence

Problem:

Face recognition in mobile phone.

Programmer does not write rules for:

Eyes
Nose
Face shape

AI learns automatically from many images.
